cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.CR

This paper discusses the formal methods perspective of achieving Verified AI, which involves the use of mathematical specifications and proofs to ensure correctness. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI, which focuses on artificial intelligence and its applications. The paper also discusses challenges and principles for achieving Verified AI, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LO (logic in computer science), cs.SE (software engineering), cs.PL (programming languages), and cs.CR (cryptography and security).
